Sentencas: A series of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.9M0.1O3 (M = Mn, Fe, Co, Ni) perovskite compounds was synthesized by a modified citrate sol-gel route and employed as anode electrodes on YSZ electrolyte supported SOFC cells.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.9M0.1O3 perovskites as anodes for CO-fuelled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Materials and anode electrodes were characterized for their chemical composition, crystal structure and film morphology.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.9M0.1O3 perovskites as anodes for CO-fuelled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the prepared anodes was evaluated in button cells under SOFC operation with CO/CO2 mixtures in the temperature range of 900-1000 A degrees C.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.9M0.1O3 perovskites as anodes for CO-fuelled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was shown that the performance of the perovskite materials in terms of maximum power density follows the sequence
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.9M0.1O3 perovskites as anodes for CO-fuelled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Fe > Ni > Co > Mn, based on the substitution cation into the B-site.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.9M0.1O3 perovskites as anodes for CO-fuelled solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: No carbon deposition was observed under the operating conditions examined, even for prolonged (120 h) exposure to the reaction mixture.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.9M0.1O3 perovskites as anodes for CO-fuelled solid oxide fuel cells
